:Cooper, Ron}}\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alabama A&M Bulldogs football coaches]]\n[[Category:Appalachian State Mountaineers football coaches]]\n[[Category:Austin Peay Governors football coaches]]\n[[Category:East Carolina Pirates football coaches]]\n[[Category:Eastern Michigan Eagles football coaches]]\n[[Category:FIU Panthers football coaches]]\n[[Category:Jacksonville State Gamecocks football players]]\n[[Category:Louisville Cardinals football coaches]]\n[[Category:LSU Tigers football coaches]]\n[[Category:Minnesota Golden Gophers football coaches]]\n[[Category:Mississippi State Bulldogs football coaches]]\n[[Category:Murray State Racers football coaches]]\n[[Category:Notre Dame Fighting Irish football coaches]]\n[[Category:South Carolina Gamecocks football coaches]]\n[[Category:South Florida Bulls football coaches]]\n[[Category:Tampa Bay Buccaneers coaches]]\n[[Category:UNLV Rebels football coaches]]\n[[Category:Wisconsin Badgers football coaches]]\n[[Category:Appalachian State University alumni]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Huntsville, Alabama]]\n[[Category:African-American coaches of American football]]\n[[Category:African-American players of American football]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American football coach}}\n{{Infobox college coach\n| name = Ron Cooper\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| current_title = Defensive backs coach\n| current_team = [[Arkansas Razorbacks football|Arkansas]]\n| current_conference = [[Southeastern Conference|SEC]]\n| current_record = \n| contract = \n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1962|2|11}}\n| birth_place = [[Huntsville, Alabama]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater = \n| player_years1 = 1979\u20131982\n| player_team1 = [[Jacksonville State Gamecocks football|Jacksonville State]]\n| coach_years1 = 1983\n| coach_team1 = [[Appalachian State Mountaineers football|Appalachian State]] ([[Graduate assistant|GA]])\n| coach_years2 = 1984\n| coach_team2 = [[Minnesota Golden Gophers football|Minnesota]] (GA)\n| coach_years3 = 1985\u20131986\n| coach_team3 = [[Austin Peay Governors football|Austin Peay]] (assistant)\n| coach_years4 = 1987\u20131988\n| coach_team4 = [[Murray State Racers football|Murray State]] (DC)\n| coach_years5 = 1989\n| coach_team5 = [[East Carolina Pirates football|East Carolina]] (assistant)\n| coach_years6 = 1990\n| coach_team6 = [[UNLV Rebels football|UNLV]] (DC)\n| coach_years7 = 1991\u20131992\n| coach_team7 = [[Notre Dame Fighting Irish football|Notre Dame]] (assistant)\n| coach_years8 = 1993\u20131994\n| coach_team8 = [[Eastern Michigan Eagles football|Eastern Michigan]]\n| coach_years9 = 1995\u20131997\n| coach_team9 = [[Louisville Cardinals football|Louisville]]\n| coach_years10 = 1998\u20132001\n| coach_team10 = [[Alabama A&M Bulldogs football|Alabama A&M]]\n| coach_years11 = 2002\n| coach_team11 = [[Wisconsin Badgers football|Wisconsin]] (DB)\n| coach_years12 = 2003\n| coach_team12 = [[Mississippi State Bulldogs football|Mississippi State]] (DC)\n| coach_years13 = 2004\n| coach_team13 = [[South Carolina Gamecocks football|South Carolina]] (DB)\n| coach_years14 = 2005\n| coach_team14 = [[South Carolina Gamecocks football|South Carolina]] (OLB/ST)\n| coach_years15 = 2006\u20132007\n| coach_team15 = [[South Carolina Gamecocks football|South Carolina]] (AHC/DB)\n| coach_years16 = 2008\n| coach_team16 = [[South Carolina Gamecocks football|South Carolina]] (S)\n| coach_years17 = 2009\u20132011\n| coach_team17 = [[LSU Tigers football|LSU]] (DB)\n| coach_years18 = 2012\n| coach_team18 = [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] (DB)\n| coach_years19 = 2013\u20132014\n| coach_team19 = [[South Florida Bulls football|South Florida]] (AHC/DB)\n| coach_years20 = 2015\n| coach_team20 = [[FIU Panthers football|FIU]] (DB)\n| coach_years21 = 2016\n| coach_team21 = [[FIU Panthers football|FIU]] (DC/LB)\n| coach_years22 = 2016\n| coach_team22 = [[FIU Panthers football|FIU]] (interim)\n| coach_years23 = 2017\n| coach_team23 = [[Texas A&M Aggies football|Texas A&M]] (DB)\n| coach_years24 = 2018\u2013present\n| coach_team24 = [[Arkansas Razorbacks football|Arkansas]] (DB) \n| overall_record = 49\u201359\n| bowl_record = \n| tournament_record = \n| championships = \n| awards = 1 [[Southwest Athletic Conference|SWAC Eastern Division]] (2000)\n| coaching_records = \n}}\n\n'''Ronald Louis Cooper''' (born February 11, 1962) is an [[American football]] coach and former player. Currently, Cooper is the defensive backs coach at [[Arkansas Razorbacks football|Arkansas]]. Cooper served as the head football coach at [[Eastern Michigan University]] (1993\u20131994), the [[University of Louisville]] (1995\u20131997), [[Alabama Agricultural and Mechanical University|Alabama A&M]] (1998\u20132001), and the interim head coach at [[Florida International University|FIU]] (2016). He was the defensive backs coach for the [[Tampa Bay Buccaneers]] in 2012. A native of [[Huntsville, Alabama]], he played [[high school football]] at [[Lee High School (Huntsville, Alabama)|Lee High School]] and [[college football]] at [[Jacksonville State University]].<ref name=\"hsvt120108\">{{cite news |first=Mark |last=McCarter |newspaper=[[The Huntsville Times]] |location=[[Huntsville, AL]] |publisher=[[Advance Publications]] |title=Ron Cooper's path to LSU and BCS title game began on fringe of Alabama A&M campus |url=http://www.al.com/sports/index.ssf/2012/01/ron_coopers_path_to_lsu_and_bc.html |date=January 8, 2012 |accessdate=December 5, 2013 |quote=Cooper played high school football at Lee, then played for Jacksonville State.}}</ref>\n\n==Coaching career==\n===Eastern Michigan===\nCooper was the head football coach at [[Eastern Michigan University]] in [[Ypsilanti, Michigan]] from 1993 to 1994. At Eastern Michigan, his teams produced a record of 9\u201313.<ref>[http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_ia/mac/eastern_michigan/coaching_records.php College Football Data Warehouse] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101205035939/http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_ia/mac/eastern_michigan/coaching_records.php |date=2010-12-05 }} Eastern Michigan all time coaching records</ref>\n\n===Louisville===\nFrom 1995 to 1997 Cooper was the head football coach at the [[University of Louisville]], replacing [[Howard Schnellenberger]]. In his final season, the Cardinals posted a 1\u201310 record. The one win came against Illinois who finished the season with no wins (0\u201311). Cooper's overall record at Louisville was 13\u201320.<ref>[http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_ia/bigeast/louisville/coaching_records.php College Football Data Warehouse] Louisville all time coaching records</ref> On November 19, 1997, Louisville fired Cooper due to a steady decline in the team's performance.<ref>{{cite web|author=Story, Mark|title=U of L drops Cooper as coach, citing 'negativity'|work=Lexington Herald-Leader|date=November 20, 1997|url=http://www.kentuckyconnect.com/heraldleader/news/112097/fcooper.html|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20000601033338/http://www.kentuckyconnect.com/heraldleader/news/112097/fcooper.html|archivedate=June 1, 2000|accessdate=July 21, 2017}}</reF>\n\n===Alabama A&M===\nCooper's last head coaching position was at [[Alabama Agricultural and Mechanical University]], from 1998 to 2001. His squad won a division championship in [[Southwest Athletic Conference]] (SWAC) during the 2000 season<ref>[http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/div_iaa/southwestern/alabama_a&m/coaching_records.php College Football Data Warehouse] Alabama A&M all time coaching records</ref> but lost the [[SWAC Championship Game]] to [[Grambling]] on December 12, 2000.<ref>[http://www.cfbdatawarehouse.com/data/coaching/alltime_coach_game_by_game.php?coachid=441&year=2000 College Football Data Warehouse] Alabama A&M 2000 season results</ref>\n\n===Other coaching duties===\nIn 2002, Cooper was the secondaries coach at the [[University of Wisconsin\u2013Madison]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://gamecocksonline.cstv.com/sports/m-footbl/mtt/cooper_ron00.html|title=GamecocksOnline.com  - South Carolina Gamecocks Official Athletic Site Official Athletic Site of the South Carolina Gamecocks - Football|publisher=}}</ref> and in 2003 the defensive coordinator and safeties coach at [[Mississippi State]]. Other coaching stops have included the [[University of South Carolina]] and the [[University of Notre Dame]]. Cooper is an alumnus of [[Jacksonville State University]].\n\n===Tampa Bay Buccaneers===\nCooper was hired by the Buccaneers on February 22, 2012 to be the teams defensive backs coach.\n\n===Florida International===\nIn 2015, Cooper became the defensive coordinator and associate head coach at [[Florida International University]]. Following [[Ron Turner (American football)|Ron Turner]]'s termination in September 2016, Cooper was named interim head coach.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fiusports.com/news/2016/9/25/football-ron-turner-relieved-of-duties.aspx |title=Ron Turner Relieved of Duties |publisher=FIU Sports |date= September 25, 2016 |accessdate=September 25, 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Head coaching record==\n{{CFB Yearly Record Start | type = coach | team = | conf = | bowl = | poll = no }}\n{{CFB Yearly Record Subhead\n | name      = [[Eastern Michigan Eagles football|Eastern Michigan Eagles]]\n | conf      = [[Mid-American Conference]]\n | startyear = 1993\n | endyear   = 1994\n}}\n{{CFB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | year         = [[1993 NCAA Division I-A football season|1993]]\n | name         = [[1993 Eastern Michigan Eagles football team|Eastern Michigan]]\n | overall      = 4\u20137\n | conference   = 3\u20135\n | confstanding = T\u20137th\n | bowlname     =\n | bowloutcome  =\n | bcsbowl      =\n | ranking      = no\n | ranking2     = no\n}}\n{{CFB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship =\n | year         = [[1994 NCAA Division I-A football season|1994]]\n | name         = [[1994 Eastern Michigan Eagles football team|Eastern Michigan]]\n | overall    